item.title: Ok all working sept nothing is showing up in the shops
item.dc:creator: @chazion chazion
item.description:
@chazion wrote:

[quote=“NotLikingThis, post:9, topic:421748”]My compiler looks nothing like yours.
This is mine:

@echo off "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -classpath deps/log4j-1.2.15.jar;deps/jython.jar;deps/xstream.jar;deps/mina.jar;deps/mysql.jar;deps/poi.jar;deps/slf4j.jar;deps/slf4j-nop.jar -d bin src\server\event\*.java src\server\model\items\*.java src\server\model\minigames\*.java src\server\model\npcs\*.java src\server\model\objects\*.java src\server\model\players\*.java src\server\model\players\skills\*.java src\server\model\players\packets\*.java src\server\model\shops\*.java src\server\net\*.java src\server\task\*.java src\server\util\*.java src\server\world\*.java src\server\util\log\*.java src\server\*.java src\server\world\map\*.java pause[/quote]

Okay, navigate to your JDK files located in C:/programfiles/java/JDK/bin or C:/programfiles (x86)/java/JDK/bin

when you get to your bin folder look up top at the files location and take note of it…

now lets take a look at your compiler

above is the only part you SHOULD need to edit

the “programfiles” part with either be “programfiles” or “programfiles (x86)” depending on where JDK is installed…

the part where is says “jdk1.7.0_1” is your JDK version…

mines is “jdk1.6.0_25” and my JDK is installed in the "programfiles (x86) folder in my “C” drive…

so the main part i need to edit in the comiler looks like this…

This may of been a bad way to explain it but I hope this helps

turbo-rsps:

ok how to make the complile work

Right click edit on the compiler bat and add this if u use 32-bit

[code]
@echo off
color 9
title Infinity Compiler

echo Compiling…

if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto er)

:er
echo You don’t have Java installed or are using a 64-bit system.

:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)

:end
echo Completed.
pause[/code]
